<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Consumer and Small Business Bank (C&SBB) serves more than 38 million consumer and small business households through a distribution network of 5,800 banking centers, 16,800 ATMs, and the nation&#39;s leading Online Banking and electronic bill pay service.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
Consumer and Small Business Banking MBA Internship Program:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Internship program designed to prepare future MBA graduates for specific senior positions within C&amp;SBB</li>
	<li>The goal is to convert MBA interns into full-time associates upon graduation   </li>
	<li>MBA Internship positions mirror the full-time positions of the Consumer and Small Business Banking MBA Leader Development Program</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Minimum of a full-time 10-12 week internship may include the following opportunities:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Business/Market Analysis</li>
	<li>Project management</li>
	<li>Product marketing and development</li>
	<li>Process, design and improvement (Structured Coaching)</li>
	<li>Customer Experience analysis</li>
	<li>Banking Center Experience</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Key Facts about Consumer and Small Business Banking:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Intern assignments are carefully selected according to the developmental needs of each individual participant.</li>
	<li>Each position offers a wide range of responsibilities and business opportunities for the intern </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Ideal candidate will exhibit a strong drive for results; succeed in a fast-paced, empowered, and collaborative environment; enjoy teamwork and partnering with others; possess excellent organizational and analytical skills; understand technology and business requirements.  The ability to learn the organizational structure and the formal/informal workings of the organization and to convey a strong sense of customer and associate satisfaction to drive shareholder value is required.  Additionally requirements include:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Must be a MBA candidate at an accredited university or college during the time of the internship (i.e., students who apply for a summer 2010 internship must not have a graduation date prior to August 2011)</li>
	<li>Candidates must be a first year MBA student</li>
	<li>Must possess the authorization to work in the United States</li>
	<li>Must be geographically flexible</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Expertise and/or experience in at least 3 of the following:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Familiarity with database marketing and segmentation principles </li>
	<li>Experience in execution/production for end to end marketing campaign management processes </li>
	<li>Previous financial services or retail experience</li>
	<li>Strong statistical background (Black Belt certified or an experienced Statistician in the deep drilling of data sets) and ability to use statistical methodology and tools (e.g., SPSS and SAS) to conduct and report on market research</li>
	<li>3+ years of pricing, valuation, and/or risk management experience</li>
	<li>Experience with SQL, Access and database management </li>
	<li>Proficiency in a second foreign language (e.g., Spanish, Korean, etc.)</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Personal characteristics:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ability to successfully navigate in a complex environment</li>
	<li>Strong leadership potential</li>
	<li>Results oriented, proven high level of performance</li>
	<li>Ability to manage tight deadlines, organize, and prioritize work independently </li>
	<li>Flexibility in exploring a variety of business areas</li>
	<li>Maturity, resourcefulness and integrity</li>
</ul>

